  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 12.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - Eternal life is not granted to the whole world, or even to all Christians ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "en masse",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; it is given to individuals, soul by soul, according as each does or does not accept the Son of God. The order of the Greek is noteworthy - in the first half of the verse the emphasis is on \"hath,\" in the second on \"life.\" Here, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 1:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the article before ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ζωή",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " should be translated, \"hath the life...  hath not the life.\" The insertion of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "τοῦ Θεοῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in the second half of the verse points to the magnitude of the loss: the possessor has no need to be told ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "whose",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Son he has. 1 John 5:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hath life (ἔχει τὴν ζωὴν)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "More strictly, as Rev., the life; i.e., the life which God gave (1 John 5:11). See on John 16:22. Compare Christ who is our life (Colossians 3:4).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "More strictly, as Rev., the life; i.e., the life which God gave (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 John 5:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
